  3. score1~score2*sex

  4. score1~score2:sex

  1. score1~sex*school

  1. score1~sex + (1 | school)

  2. score1~sex + (sex | school)

Homework: please get from the fitted lm_m1 the predictions for the score 1 for boys and girls, if score 2 is 50.

ennustame keskmist skoori nii le kikide koolide kui ka kooli tasemel eraldi poistele ja tdrukutele.

get_prior(score1~sex + (sex | school), 
          data= schools)
prior <- c(prior(normal(50, 30), class="b"),
           prior(normal(0, 20), class ="b", coef = "sex1"),
           prior(lkj(3), class = "cor"))
sch_m1 <- brm(score1~sex + (sex | school), 
          data= schools, prior = prior, chains = 3, cores = 3)
write_rds(sch_m1, path = "sch_m1.fit")
sch_m1 <- read_rds("sch_m1.fit")

b_Intercept annab ennustuse sex = 0 keskmisele testitulemusele le kikide koolide ja b_sex1 annab sex = 1 tulemuse. Kooli tasemele minnes tuleb teha tehted:

b_Intercept + r_school[xxx,Intercept] ja

b_sex1 + r_school[xxx,sex1],

et saada sellele koolile ennustatud poiste ja tdrukute skoor.

tidyMCMC(sch_m1$fit, conf.int = TRUE, conf.method = "HPDinterval",
    rhat = TRUE)

Kui suure tenosusega on sex1 koef suurem kui -2.3?
